		Hello, I am preparing a pull request for displaying users's quota used/left. To do so I created a new RemoteOperation copying the GetRemoteUserNameOperation available. However, I am continuously getting 400 Bad Response back from the server, while with a simple Curl everything works nice and smooth. Since with a basic inspection of the headers I couldn't figure out I sniffed my own packets with Wireshark and found the problem: Working request: http://en.zimagez.com/zimage/rightreq.php Non working request: http://en.zimagez.com/zimage/wrongreq.php If you want to try it out we have a server up and running at 54.77.93.38 user/pass = demo demo . And finally here is the code I used: curl that works: curl -H "Authorization: Basic ZGVtbzpkZW1v" http://54.77.93.38/ocs/v1.php/cloud/users/demo Java code that doesn't   private static final String OCS_ROUTE ="/ocs/v1.php/cloud/users/";

   String url = client.getBaseUri() + OCS_ROUTE + credentials.getUsername();
   get = new GetMethod(url);
   get.addRequestHeader(createAuthenticationHeader(credentials));
   get.setQueryString(new NameValuePair[]{new NameValuePair("format","json")});
   status = client.executeMethod(get);

private Header createAuthenticationHeader(OwnCloudCredentials credentials){
    Header h = new Header();
    h.setName("Authorization");
    String authString = credentials.getUsername()+":"+credentials.getAuthToken();
    String encodedString = Base64.encodeToString(authString.getBytes(), **Base64.DEFAULT**);
    h.setValue("Basic "+encodedString);
    return h;
}
 The problem are these extra termination characters added that obviously screw everything up. I have no knowledge of the apache commons httpclient, but Google didn't return any known issue. EDIT: I found the problem. the Android Base64.DEFAULT appends a \n to the end of the string. You must use the .NO_WRAP flag

		When opening the details view of a file when NOT coming from the file list view (FileDisplayActivity) but for example clicking on the upload success notification or by calling:         Intent showDetailsIntent = new Intent(this, FileDisplayActivity.class);
